      id: 'exercises',
      title: 'The Exercises',
      humorLevel: 'medium',
      content: `How to actually train your neck:

**1. Neck Curls (Flexion)**
- Lie face up on bench, head hanging off
- Place weight plate on forehead (use towel)
- Tuck chin to chest, then return
- 3-4 sets of 15-25 reps
- Targets: Front of neck (SCM)

**2. Neck Extensions**
- Lie face down on bench, head hanging off
- Place weight plate on back of head
- Extend neck back, then return
- 3-4 sets of 15-25 reps
- Targets: Back of neck

**3. Lateral Neck Flexion**
- Lie on side, head hanging off bench
- Place weight plate on side of head
- Laterally flex neck, then return
- 3-4 sets of 15-25 reps each side
- Targets: Side of neck

**4. Neck Harness Work**
- Strap harness on head, hang weight
- Flex neck against resistance
- All directions: front, back, sides
- Great for progressive overload

**5. Wrestler Bridges (Advanced)**
- Bridge on head supporting body weight
- Front bridge and back bridge
- Very advanced—don't start here
- Build base strength first

**6. Partner Resistance (No Equipment)**
- Partner provides resistance with hands
- All directions
- Excellent for controlled resistance
- Great for beginners`,
